products.description: Blueberries are perennial flowering plants with blue or purple berries. They are classified in the section Cyanococcus within the genus Vaccinium. Vaccinium also includes cranberries, bilberries, huckleberries and Madeira blueberries. Commercial blueberries—both wild and cultivated —are all native to North America.

products.name: Brussels Sprout
products.description: The Brussels sprout is a member of the Gemmifera Group of cabbages, grown for its edible buds.
